                                        <h4>How to prevent vehicle fires?</h4>
                                        <p>A filling station staff and motorists must be aware and careful, otherwise there may be a disaster.</p>
                                        <p>A vehicle shouldn't be overloaded and driven for long time without stopping.</p>
                                        <p>Vehicle fires may result from violent collisions or overturning. It's even worse if the doors are jammed and the passengers unable to get out. Please drive carefully.</p>
                                        <p>Don't leave children alone in a vehicle, especially if the engine is running.</p>
                                        <p>Ensure that an appropriate fire extinguisher, preferably a carbon dioxide one, is fixed near the driver's seat.</p>
                                        <p>Change the engine oil regularly, and always ensure that the radiator is full.</p>
                                    }
